@node "FREEWARE" "FREEware"

 I am releasing these objects as freeware because this is my way of givingĀbackĀto allĀtheĀother Amiga user that have written some really cool programs.


 tHE ARCHIVE CAN BE FREELY DISTRIBUTED AS LONG AS ALL FILES REMAIN INTACT.ĀIFĀYOU WANTĀTOĀCONVERT THEM INTO ANOTHER FORMAT, YOU MAY REPLACE THE OBJECTS,ĀBUTĀKEEP THIS GUIDEĀFILEĀAND ADD ANY INFORMATION NEEDED TO IT.  (IF YOU NEEDĀANĀOTHER FORMAT @{"E-MAILĀME" link "author" 0} AND IĀWILLĀRUN THEM THROUGH PIXEL PRO AND SEND THEMĀTOĀYOU). IF YOU INCLUDE IT ON A CD (EXCEPTĀTHEĀAMINET) YOU MUST SEND ME A COPYĀOFĀTHE CD.
@endnode

@node "Travel Pod" "Travel Pod"

 Travelpod.ibj

 Travel Pod from Star Trek movies

 Scale: 1 imagine unit = 1 meter

 I designed the object without bit-maps so it should convert into other formatsĀeasly.ĀAlso, I started working on a star fleet officer to put in the Pod but I don't knowĀif I'llĀever get around to finishing it.  If you would like to work on it (it needs theĀblackĀpiping on the jacket, all the pins, and to have the bones defined) @{"e-mail me" link "author" 0} and I'llĀsendĀyou a copy.


 Key the Global fx "Haze" to r=245, G=245, B=255. This the theĀcolorĀofĀtheĀlightsĀandĀwillĀgive them a nice glow.

 The @{b}TravelPod.fak@{ub} is a small stand-in model to useĀinĀtheĀstageĀeditorĀ(becauseĀitĀloadsĀfaster and redraws faster).  Build the sceneĀusingĀtheĀfakeĀthenĀgo toĀthe actionĀeditorĀand replace the fak with the object.

 To animate the running Lights use @{"STATES." link "States" 0}


 @{u}TEXTURES@{uu}:
   -Dirt               Standard Imagine Texture
   -Linear             Standard Imagine Texture
   -Metals             Standard Imagine Texture
   -leather            Standard Imagine Texture
   -Fireball           Standard Imagine Texture
   -RectChex           Standard Imagine Texture
   -softEdge           Standard Imagine Lite Texture
@endnode

@node "States" "States"

 STATES
  -DEFAULT          DOORS CLOSED ALL LIGHTS ON
  -OPEN DOORS       DOORS OPEN
  -NAV & RUN ON     NAV LIGHTS AND RUNNING LIGHTS ON
  -NAV OFF, RUN ON  NAV LIGHTS OFF AND RUNNING LIGHTS ON
  -NAV & RUN OFF    NAV LIGHTS AND RUNNING LIGHTS Off
  -NAV ON, RUN OFF  NAV LIGHTS ON AND RUNNING LIGHTS Off


 At 30 frames per second The running lightsĀareĀonĀforĀ11ĀframesĀandĀoffĀforĀ11Āframes,ĀandĀthe NAV lights areĀonĀforĀoneĀframeĀeveryĀ30Āframes. Ā WellĀthat isĀhow theĀmovieĀmodelĀworksĀoff myĀlaserdisc.ĀĀIĀjustĀcheat andĀhaveĀthe runningĀlights onĀforĀ10Āframes and off for 10 frames.


